text: The vitriol has compounded on Twitter over the years. Most are shrouded in anonymity and tweet stuff they don't have the nerve to say in public when their real name is attached. Out out damn Spot (Macbeth). IMHO Twitter has become a less valuable asset, as a result.
As I have said, Republicans are hostage to their majority while Democrats are hostage to their minority. My view.

My political partisanship is my own business - which, unlike most others, I have kept to myself for over a year. What does my comment referencing a moving speech by the President have to do with my political views?
